\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 38. C. tournefortii} Gay,{\i  loc. cit.} (1831). Like {\b 36} but corm-tunic papery, splitting into parallel, vertical fibres; flowers lilac, rarely with darker veins; throat yellow or sometimes whitish, glabrous or pubescent; perianth-tube 3-10 cm; segments 1·5-3·5 × 0·4-1·3 cm, obovate or elliptical; filaments densely pubescent; capsule 1-1·2 cm, ellipsoid. Flowering from September to December. 2n = 30.{\i  Scrub and stony ground. S. Aegean region} ({\i Kikladhes, Idhra, Karpathos}). Cr Gr.
