\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 39. C. cancellatus} Herbert,{\i  Bot. Mag.}{\b  67}: sub t. 3864 (1841). Corm-tunic strongly fibrous, coarsely reticulate. Leaves 4-5, 1-2 mm wide, absent or very rarely appearing at anthesis. Flowers 1-3, white to deep blue-purple, often with darker veins; throat usually yellowish, glabrous or pubescent. Prophyll absent. Bract and bracteole subequal to unequal, membranous, white. Perianth-tube 5-15 cm, white or tinged with purple; segments 2·5-5 × 0·8-1·8 cm, oblanceolate or obovate. Filaments pale yellow, glabrous or papillose-pubescent. Anthers deep yellow. Style yellow to deep orange, shorter than or exceeding the stamens, divided into several slender branches. Capsule and seeds not known. Flowering from September to November. 2n = 16.{\i  Rocky hillsides and open woods. Greece, S. Jugoslavia.} Gr Ju.
\par

