\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 40. C. robertianus} C. D. Brickell, {\i Jour. Roy. Hort. Soc.}{\b  98}: 362 (1973). Corm-tunic strongly fibrous, coarsely reticulate. Leaves 3-4, 4-6 mm wide, absent at anthesis. Flowers 1-2, pale to lilac; throat pale yellow or whitish, glabrous or pubescent. Prophyll absent. Bract and bracteole unequal, well-exserted from the cataphylls, greenish towards the apex. Perianth-tube 4-18 cm, purplish or whitish; segments 2·5-6 × 0·9-2·1 cm, equal or subequal, oblanceolate to more or less elliptical, rounded to obtuse. Filaments whitish or pale yellow, glabrous or minutely papillose. Anthers yellow. Style orange-red, usually exceeding the stamens, shortly divided into 3 much-expanded and fimbriate branches. Capsule and seeds not known. Flowering from October to November. 2n = 20.{\i  Clearings in scrub. • N. Greece} ({\i Pindhos Oros, between Ioannina and Metsovon}). Gr.
